message.content:
There are three main types of verbs:
1. Action verbs: These describe actions that are performed by nouns or pronouns. Examples include run, jump, swim, and eat.
2. Linking verbs: These connect the subject to an adjective or a noun. Examples include be, appear, seem, and become.
3. Helping verbs: These help form tenses of other verbs. They also indicate modality (i.e., whether an action is certain or not). Examples include can, will, would, and must.
